{"TopicId":154718,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Is there a way to change the end a subassembly connects from?","CreatedByName":"Wikkyd","CreatedById":173518,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T04:20:38Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wikkyd","CreatedById":173518,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T04:20:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI created a sub-assembly, but I need to connect it from the opposite end it was created from... Is there a way to do this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T04:46:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is, but it\u0027s kind of obscure. Open it in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E to work on it, use the root tool to change the root part to the one by which you want it to attach, and then save it to subassemblies again.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, your question has been moved to the Gameplay subforum, and welcome to our forum. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T17:04:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also use the re-root tool on assemblies floating unattached to the craft you are working on.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Palaceviking","CreatedById":166883,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T17:07:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222915759\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154718\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483981472\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Foxster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Foxster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also use the re-root tool on assemblies floating unattached to the craft you are working on.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice. Didn\u0027t know that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T17:08:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222915765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154718\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483981649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Palaceviking\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Palaceviking said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice. Didn\u0027t know that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think it is widely known. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}